10
00:00:49.799 --> 00:00:54.971
<i><font color="#ffff00">The Good Bad Mother</font></i>

11
00:00:57.140 --> 00:01:00.009
- Goodbye, piggies.
- Goodness.

12
00:01:00.351 --> 00:01:03.372
You still feel sad every time
you send them away, don't you?

13
00:01:03.396 --> 00:01:05.041
Of course I do.

14
00:01:05.065 --> 00:01:08.559
I lived with and fed them
longer than my husband and kid.

15
00:01:09.944 --> 00:01:11.797
Goodbye.

16
00:01:11.821 --> 00:01:14.759
I'll take good care of your piglets.

17
00:01:14.783 --> 00:01:16.761
Don't worry about a thing.

18
00:01:16.785 --> 00:01:18.387
I'll get going then.

19
00:01:18.411 --> 00:01:20.029
- One second.
- Yes?

20
00:01:22.207 --> 00:01:25.144
These potatoes are plump and
delicious. Eat them with your kids.

21
00:01:25.168 --> 00:01:28.370
Goodness, you're always so kind.

22
00:01:28.546 --> 00:01:32.416
By the way, how's your son doing?

23
00:01:47.065 --> 00:01:49.043
- Ready or not!
- Ready or not!

24
00:01:49.067 --> 00:01:51.763
{\an8}- Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!
- Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

25
00:01:51.787 --> 00:01:53.395
{\an8}- Shoot!
- Shoot!

26
00:01:53.905 --> 00:01:57.525
{\an8}All right! I won!

27
00:01:57.951 --> 00:01:59.777
{\an8}Okay!

28
00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:08.911
{\an8}Here we go!

29
00:02:13.049 --> 00:02:17.461
{\an8}Mom!

30
00:02:20.223 --> 00:02:22.559
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">The Good Bad Mother</font></i>

31
00:02:25.854 --> 00:02:27.039
Are you done?

32
00:02:27.063 --> 00:02:29.667
Yes, it's good as new.

33
00:02:29.691 --> 00:02:31.418
- Goodness.
- It's perfect.

34
00:02:31.442 --> 00:02:35.005
My gosh, you're such a crafty handyman.

35
00:02:35.029 --> 00:02:39.218
Your family is skilled with your hands.

36
00:02:39.242 --> 00:02:40.386
You know,

37
00:02:40.410 --> 00:02:44.598
I'm feeling sort of offended to hear that.

38
00:02:44.622 --> 00:02:47.560
Is it because I have a delinquent son?

39
00:02:47.584 --> 00:02:50.437
Don't take things that far.

40
00:02:50.461 --> 00:02:54.191
Anyway, I'm relieved that nobody got hurt.

41
00:02:54.215 --> 00:02:56.652
- Yes.
- This could've been much worse.

42
00:02:56.676 --> 00:02:58.279
Push me.

43
00:02:58.303 --> 00:03:00.447
- Here I go.
- It's smooth.

44
00:03:00.471 --> 00:03:02.673
- This is nice.
- Yes.

45
00:03:03.641 --> 00:03:07.136
They said you'd love it...

46
00:03:07.353 --> 00:03:08.455
if I exercised.

47
00:03:08.479 --> 00:03:10.264
Who did?

48
00:03:11.733 --> 00:03:12.877
Goodness.

49
00:03:12.901 --> 00:03:17.965
Goodness, Mommy's little
boy wanted to make her happy.

50
00:03:17.989 --> 00:03:20.259
What a wonderful son.

51
00:03:20.283 --> 00:03:23.137
Of course he is.

52
00:03:23.161 --> 00:03:26.807
And those clever twins went after his weakness.

53
00:03:26.831 --> 00:03:28.726
Kids.

54
00:03:28.750 --> 00:03:31.812
How many times do I have
to tell you this is dangerous?

55
00:03:31.836 --> 00:03:35.566
That's not a toy. That's his legs.

56
00:03:35.590 --> 00:03:38.542
That's not my legs. It's a wheelchair.

57
00:03:39.510 --> 00:03:44.200
Anyway, don't ever play
around with it again, okay?

58
00:03:44.224 --> 00:03:47.995
It's not for muddy roads, icy
roads, bumpy stony paths, waterways,

59
00:03:48.019 --> 00:03:49.496
rice paddy ridges, banks,

60
00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:51.582
and especially anywhere up high.

61
00:03:51.606 --> 00:03:52.791
Okay?

62
00:03:52.815 --> 00:03:54.772
And it's not for three people to ride, right?

63
00:03:54.796 --> 00:03:55.878
Of course not!

64
00:03:55.902 --> 00:03:57.603
See?

65
00:03:58.821 --> 00:04:02.551
What about using the rubber tube as a hula hoop?

66
00:04:02.575 --> 00:04:03.510
What?

67
00:04:03.534 --> 00:04:04.553
Kang-ho.

68
00:04:04.577 --> 00:04:06.305
Goodness, Kang-ho...

69
00:04:06.329 --> 00:04:07.598
Goodness. Hey!

70
00:04:07.622 --> 00:04:09.266
You darned...

71
00:04:09.290 --> 00:04:11.143
little twins!

72
00:04:11.167 --> 00:04:12.394
You rascals!

73
00:04:12.418 --> 00:04:13.646
- Goodness.
- Stop.

74
00:04:13.670 --> 00:04:14.897
Don't do that.

75
00:04:14.921 --> 00:04:16.190
I already talked to them.

76
00:04:16.214 --> 00:04:20.110
Why did you drag him out and bully him?

77
00:04:20.134 --> 00:04:21.654
We didn't bully him!

78
00:04:21.678 --> 00:04:23.864
We helped him exercise!

79
00:04:23.888 --> 00:04:26.340
How are you going to help him do that?

80
00:04:26.516 --> 00:04:28.160
Look at him!

81
00:04:28.184 --> 00:04:31.288
And you can't treat him like that!

82
00:04:31.312 --> 00:04:32.665
He's not your friend!

83
00:04:32.689 --> 00:04:34.750
What? We weren't friends?

84
00:04:34.774 --> 00:04:36.001
I thought we were friends.

85
00:04:36.025 --> 00:04:37.336
You said you were seven!

86
00:04:37.360 --> 00:04:38.504
I am!

87
00:04:38.528 --> 00:04:40.214
The doctor said I'm seven!

88
00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:42.106
Right, Mom?

89
00:05:02.552 --> 00:05:05.087
Beans will grow from your tummy.

90
00:05:32.707 --> 00:05:34.393
35.

91
00:05:34.417 --> 00:05:35.811
Repeat after me.

92
00:05:35.835 --> 00:05:36.854
35.

93
00:05:36.878 --> 00:05:38.522
That's right.

94
00:05:38.546 --> 00:05:41.874
Kang-ho, you're 35.

95
00:05:42.592 --> 00:05:45.946
But you became a little sick.

96
00:05:45.970 --> 00:05:50.424
So you became seven for a short while.

97
00:05:51.309 --> 00:05:52.619
I know what that means.

98
00:05:52.643 --> 00:05:54.163
What?

99
00:05:54.187 --> 00:05:56.096
I'm stupid, right?

100
00:05:56.814 --> 00:05:59.543
No! Who said that?

101
00:05:59.567 --> 00:06:01.935
- Who said that to you?
- You did!

102
00:06:02.279 --> 00:06:03.255
What?

103
00:06:03.279 --> 00:06:05.799
You and the doctor said that.

104
00:06:05.823 --> 00:06:07.301
"Simply put, he's..."

105
00:06:07.325 --> 00:06:09.136
"Simply put, he's..."

106
00:06:09.160 --> 00:06:10.387
...stupid?

107
00:06:10.411 --> 00:06:12.404
"...stupid."

108
00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:21.163
No, Kang-ho.

109
00:06:21.214 --> 00:06:24.333
I said that because I didn't know any better.

110
00:06:24.509 --> 00:06:26.361
So here's the thing.

111
00:06:26.385 --> 00:06:28.045
Yes.

112
00:06:28.387 --> 00:06:29.865
Kang-ho,

113
00:06:29.889 --> 00:06:32.633
you went back to your childhood.

114
00:06:33.142 --> 00:06:37.081
Everyone wants to be young again.

115
00:06:37.105 --> 00:06:40.557
I do too. I want to go back too.

116
00:06:40.775 --> 00:06:44.353
Because if I could, I'd be
able to change many things.

117
00:06:44.821 --> 00:06:49.900
But nobody in this world can turn back time.

118
00:06:50.576 --> 00:06:53.070
Yet you did, Kang-ho.

119
00:06:53.412 --> 00:06:55.155
This is...

120
00:06:55.289 --> 00:06:57.491
a chance given from above.

121
00:06:58.042 --> 00:07:01.078
A chance to start all over again.

122
00:07:02.588 --> 00:07:05.332
"A chance given from above"?

123
00:07:05.383 --> 00:07:08.877
Yes, that's right.

124
00:07:11.639 --> 00:07:14.493
So you should be happy.

125
00:07:14.517 --> 00:07:17.636
Don't be sad or devastated.

126
00:07:17.937 --> 00:07:19.721
Be happy.

127
00:07:19.939 --> 00:07:22.432
- Happy?
- Yes.

128
00:07:22.733 --> 00:07:24.518
Your return...

129
00:07:24.944 --> 00:07:27.479
makes me feel...

130
00:07:29.740 --> 00:07:31.733
happy.

131
00:07:34.495 --> 00:07:36.321
Happy.

132
00:07:41.252 --> 00:07:42.995
That's right.

133
00:07:56.100 --> 00:07:57.536
Hello.

134
00:07:57.560 --> 00:08:01.748
Squid and mackerel are extra fresh today.

135
00:08:01.772 --> 00:08:04.209
- What would you like?
- Well...

136
00:08:04.233 --> 00:08:06.879
Are you Sun-young's mother?

137
00:08:06.903 --> 00:08:08.422
- I...
- What is it?

138
00:08:08.446 --> 00:08:12.357
Did that wench run off with your money too?

139
00:08:12.867 --> 00:08:16.320
- Sorry?
- That crazy wench!

140
00:08:16.621 --> 00:08:20.684
I can't live like this!

141
00:08:20.708 --> 00:08:22.618
Good grief!

142
00:08:23.377 --> 00:08:27.774
She met this gigolo somewhere,

143
00:08:27.798 --> 00:08:31.111
and gave him every single penny she had.

144
00:08:31.135 --> 00:08:35.532
Then she even took out a private
loan to pay back his gambling debt.

145
00:08:35.556 --> 00:08:37.257
Good grief.

146
00:08:37.433 --> 00:08:39.077
She put up her home, salon,

147
00:08:39.101 --> 00:08:42.289
and even her father's
fishing boat as collateral.

148
00:08:42.313 --> 00:08:45.307
Goodness me.

149
00:08:45.399 --> 00:08:47.085
That darned brat...

150
00:08:47.109 --> 00:08:49.755
never even called me once after that,

151
00:08:49.779 --> 00:08:52.466
then texted me saying she
was going to Los Angeles,

152
00:08:52.490 --> 00:08:54.510
or whatever, to make money.

153
00:08:54.534 --> 00:08:55.886
Good grief.

154
00:08:55.910 --> 00:09:00.405
All she left was that one
message before she disappeared.

155
00:09:04.502 --> 00:09:07.397
- What do I do?
- I raised her wrong.

156
00:09:07.421 --> 00:09:10.025
Who else is to blame?

157
00:09:10.049 --> 00:09:12.152
You can just take me.

158
00:09:12.176 --> 00:09:14.878
Just take me away!

159
00:09:15.638 --> 00:09:17.798
No.

160
00:09:18.057 --> 00:09:22.427
It must've been so tough for you.

161
00:09:22.645 --> 00:09:25.374
You're much better than my daughter.

162
00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:28.502
Just be my daughter!

163
00:09:28.526 --> 00:09:31.645
Mom!

164
00:09:40.288 --> 00:09:44.083
<i><font color="#ffa07a">Legal proceedings will be initiated
due to long-overdue payments.</font></i>

165
00:09:44.959 --> 00:09:46.460
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffa07a">Landlady</font></i>

166
00:09:48.879 --> 00:09:50.190
Hello, ma'am.

167
00:09:50.214 --> 00:09:52.374
<i>Are you really going to be like this?</i>

168
00:09:52.466 --> 00:09:55.904
<i>I even gave you back your deposit in advance.</i>

169
00:09:55.928 --> 00:09:59.074
<i>Your rent payments have been long overdue.</i>

170
00:09:59.098 --> 00:10:00.450
<i>I can't wait any longer.</i>

171
00:10:00.474 --> 00:10:03.431
<i>I'm going to vacate the place if
you don't transfer the money today.</i>

172
00:10:03.455 --> 00:10:05.365
Well, I...

173
00:10:17.366 --> 00:10:20.161
<i><font color="#ffa07a">Seo-jin, Ye-jin
I made this bank book for you</font></i>

174
00:10:21.787 --> 00:10:24.373
<i><font color="#ffa07a">I want to let you do everything you want</font></i>

175
00:10:26.667 --> 00:10:28.628
<i><font color="#ffa07a">Ye-jin, Seo-jin
Give Mom the power to go on</font></i>

176
00:10:55.279 --> 00:10:56.980
Stay there.

177
00:10:57.948 --> 00:11:01.818
A warm welcome to Petit Nail, Sillim Branch!

178
00:11:03.079 --> 00:11:05.599
How many years of experience do you have?

179
00:11:05.623 --> 00:11:07.434
I got certified in school,

180
00:11:07.458 --> 00:11:09.937
and worked at the Ewha Branch
for three and a half years.

181
00:11:09.961 --> 00:11:12.857
And I'm joining this branch
because I moved to Sillim-dong.

182
00:11:12.881 --> 00:11:13.690
Welcome.

183
00:11:13.714 --> 00:11:15.233
Your manager told us...

184
00:11:15.257 --> 00:11:19.196
you were popular among college girls
for your quick hands and nail arts.

185
00:11:19.220 --> 00:11:20.906
I look forward to working with you.

186
00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:22.839
Yes, I'll do my best.

187
00:11:23.349 --> 00:11:24.826
- My gosh.
- It's here.

188
00:11:24.850 --> 00:11:26.286
The raw fish here is delicious.

189
00:11:26.310 --> 00:11:29.498
The owner catches the fish himself.

190
00:11:29.522 --> 00:11:32.641
So this is caught in the wild?

191
00:11:35.486 --> 00:11:36.505
Kang-ho?

192
00:11:36.529 --> 00:11:38.173
No, not kelpfish. It's rockfish.

193
00:11:38.197 --> 00:11:39.591
Wild rockfish.

194
00:11:39.615 --> 00:11:41.176
A bottle of <i>soju,</i> please.

195
00:11:41.200 --> 00:11:42.219
Mi-joo?

196
00:11:42.243 --> 00:11:44.402
No, not Mi-joo. <i>Soju.</i>

197
00:11:58.717 --> 00:12:02.379
Where have you been, you jerk?

198
00:12:13.023 --> 00:12:17.310
I can't believe you've never
called after moving to Seoul.

199
00:12:18.195 --> 00:12:20.132
I waited for so long.

200
00:12:20.156 --> 00:12:22.759
Why didn't you call first?

201
00:12:22.783 --> 00:12:25.262
I didn't have your number.

202
00:12:25.286 --> 00:12:27.514
Your mom wouldn't tell me either.

203
00:12:27.538 --> 00:12:29.307
You knew the school I was attending.

204
00:12:29.331 --> 00:12:31.825
I wanted to look for you.

205
00:12:32.751 --> 00:12:34.828
But I couldn't.

206
00:12:35.337 --> 00:12:38.150
You ruined your exam because of me.

207
00:12:38.174 --> 00:12:40.333
I couldn't ruin anything more.

208
00:12:43.596 --> 00:12:45.255
Wait.

209
00:12:47.349 --> 00:12:50.677
Did you give up on the bar exam?

210
00:12:51.645 --> 00:12:54.374
I took the first test yesterday.

211
00:12:54.398 --> 00:12:57.127
Isn't it a little too early to give up?

212
00:12:57.151 --> 00:12:58.977
I see.

213
00:13:00.779 --> 00:13:02.856
Then what are you doing here?

214
00:13:02.991 --> 00:13:04.035
Working a part-time job.

215
00:13:04.059 --> 00:13:06.511
Shouldn't you be studying every second?

216
00:13:06.535 --> 00:13:08.680
I'm doing this to survive.

217
00:13:08.704 --> 00:13:10.765
I have to make a living too.

218
00:13:10.789 --> 00:13:14.284
What do you mean? Doesn't your mom help you?

219
00:13:15.544 --> 00:13:18.440
I'm old enough to look after myself.

220
00:13:18.464 --> 00:13:20.817
But every second counts for you.

221
00:13:20.841 --> 00:13:23.403
If I fail the exam because of a part-time job,

222
00:13:23.427 --> 00:13:26.129
it means I'm just not good enough.

223
00:13:26.764 --> 00:13:28.200
Don't worry.

224
00:13:28.224 --> 00:13:30.452
It's a restaurant, so I get free food,

225
00:13:30.476 --> 00:13:33.220
the lady here sometimes helps with my laundry,

226
00:13:33.354 --> 00:13:36.264
and on weekends, I get to go fishing too.

227
00:13:36.774 --> 00:13:38.558
Above all,

228
00:13:39.693 --> 00:13:42.729
I like looking at these fish.

229
00:13:43.906 --> 00:13:46.385
What's great about staring
at fish that are about to die?

230
00:13:46.409 --> 00:13:48.277
Exactly.

231
00:13:48.577 --> 00:13:50.931
They might die any moment now,

232
00:13:50.955 --> 00:13:53.934
but no matter how painful or scary it is,

233
00:13:53.958 --> 00:13:56.368
they're unable to cry or scream.

234
00:13:57.670 --> 00:14:00.330
I think judicial officers must be like that.

235
00:14:01.131 --> 00:14:05.168
You hated how your fate was
decided the moment you were born.

236
00:14:06.011 --> 00:14:08.755
I guess you've changed your mind.

237
00:14:09.265 --> 00:14:10.966
No.

238
00:14:11.684 --> 00:14:13.468
Nothing's changed.

239
00:14:13.686 --> 00:14:16.748
I still hate it, and it's still a heavy burden.

240
00:14:16.772 --> 00:14:21.434
But I hate this heavy burden so
much that I'll make sure I make it.

241
00:14:21.610 --> 00:14:25.382
That's the revenge for my fate,
which was already decided...

242
00:14:25.406 --> 00:14:27.816
the moment I was born.

243
00:14:36.417 --> 00:14:39.578
So Mi-joo, how are you doing? How's your job?

244
00:14:45.885 --> 00:14:48.154
Things have never gone well for me,

245
00:14:48.178 --> 00:14:51.006
and I never had a reason to be successful.

246
00:14:51.390 --> 00:14:53.550
But I'm going to start doing well.

247
00:14:54.643 --> 00:14:57.220
I just found something I want to do.

248
00:14:58.105 --> 00:15:00.500
You just focus on your studies.

249
00:15:00.524 --> 00:15:04.087
You might be able to pass it
with the top score if you don't work.

250
00:15:04.111 --> 00:15:06.313
Let me invest in you.

251
00:15:06.822 --> 00:15:10.609
I don't have much right now,
so I'll start with myself.

252
00:15:11.827 --> 00:15:14.988
Let me help you get your revenge.

253
00:15:21.170 --> 00:15:23.455
Thank you for everything.

254
00:15:23.672 --> 00:15:26.166
We never had any kids,

255
00:15:26.258 --> 00:15:28.069
so you were like a son to us.

256
00:15:28.093 --> 00:15:29.878
This is so sad.

257
00:15:30.054 --> 00:15:31.781
Don't be so sad.

258
00:15:31.805 --> 00:15:35.508
He'll study hard and become a judicial officer.

259
00:15:35.893 --> 00:15:37.954
Visit me...

260
00:15:37.978 --> 00:15:39.539
when you need to blow off steam.

261
00:15:39.563 --> 00:15:41.207
I'll give you a ride.

