00:30:32.539 --> 00:30:36.951
Prosecutor Choi will ensure
discretion throughout it.

525
00:30:48.096 --> 00:30:50.950
I'm really curious...

526
00:30:50.974 --> 00:30:55.663
about your parents, who brought you
up to be such a promising prosecutor.

527
00:30:55.687 --> 00:30:58.472
What are your parents like?

528
00:30:59.440 --> 00:31:00.501
So...

529
00:31:00.525 --> 00:31:04.520
what does your father do?

530
00:31:05.864 --> 00:31:08.023
He passed away.

531
00:31:09.200 --> 00:31:11.345
Goodness.

532
00:31:11.369 --> 00:31:14.029
I shouldn't have asked.

533
00:31:14.455 --> 00:31:16.016
I'm sorry.

534
00:31:16.040 --> 00:31:17.601
It's all right.

535
00:31:17.625 --> 00:31:19.603
He passed away before I was born.

536
00:31:19.627 --> 00:31:21.647
I don't have any memory of him.

537
00:31:21.671 --> 00:31:23.664
He passed away...

538
00:31:23.756 --> 00:31:25.901
even before you were born?

539
00:31:25.925 --> 00:31:28.737
He must've passed away at a very young age.

540
00:31:28.761 --> 00:31:30.546
What happened?

541
00:31:32.849 --> 00:31:35.411
I heard he took his own life.

542
00:31:35.435 --> 00:31:37.136
Suicide?

543
00:31:37.312 --> 00:31:38.747
Why did he do that?

544
00:31:38.771 --> 00:31:41.876
His farm went under after a fire,

545
00:31:41.900 --> 00:31:45.170
and he was apparently under a lot of stress.

546
00:31:45.194 --> 00:31:47.605
I don't know anything more.

547
00:31:49.157 --> 00:31:50.816
Well...

548
00:31:50.992 --> 00:31:55.154
To be frank, I don't want to know.

549
00:31:55.997 --> 00:31:58.058
To me, my father...

550
00:31:58.082 --> 00:32:01.395
was just an irresponsible man...

551
00:32:01.419 --> 00:32:03.954
who abandoned his wife and unborn child.

552
00:32:07.133 --> 00:32:11.045
Anyhow, I'm sorry.

553
00:32:11.304 --> 00:32:13.881
Have a drink with me.

554
00:32:26.361 --> 00:32:28.756
Prosecutor Choi, let me ask you something.

555
00:32:28.780 --> 00:32:30.898
What's the reason?

556
00:32:31.199 --> 00:32:34.386
- Sorry?
- This trial, I mean.

557
00:32:34.410 --> 00:32:37.738
Are you after money or power?

558
00:32:39.165 --> 00:32:41.033
If I want it,

559
00:32:41.459 --> 00:32:43.577
can you give it to me?

560
00:32:44.420 --> 00:32:46.649
You just saved my grandson.

561
00:32:46.673 --> 00:32:48.832
So why not?

562
00:32:52.095 --> 00:32:54.630
In that case, both.

563
00:32:56.892 --> 00:32:57.868
Man.

564
00:32:57.892 --> 00:33:00.719
You're a man, aren't you?

565
00:33:00.853 --> 00:33:02.805
Mr. Soh.

566
00:33:06.067 --> 00:33:07.768
Go on.

567
00:33:16.244 --> 00:33:18.472
In return,

568
00:33:18.496 --> 00:33:21.115
you'll be a part of my family now.

569
00:33:23.501 --> 00:33:25.327
Thank you.

570
00:33:27.630 --> 00:33:28.649
Thank you.

571
00:33:28.673 --> 00:33:30.332
Thank you very much.

572
00:33:30.383 --> 00:33:32.376
That's enough.

573
00:33:32.719 --> 00:33:35.322
I'll do my best, Mr. Song. Thank you!

574
00:33:35.346 --> 00:33:39.785
I don't care what Kang-ho had on his mind...

575
00:33:39.809 --> 00:33:41.328
when he approached me.

576
00:33:41.352 --> 00:33:44.763
I don't care if it's ambition or wrath.

577
00:33:45.064 --> 00:33:48.210
Because his hands are now also dirty.

578
00:33:48.234 --> 00:33:52.229
All I want to do is use his talent,

579
00:33:52.280 --> 00:33:56.150
and then I'll abandon him.

580
00:34:08.671 --> 00:34:10.691
Goodness, Mr. Son.

581
00:34:10.715 --> 00:34:13.986
What on earth are you doing? It's been an hour.

582
00:34:14.010 --> 00:34:19.158
It's because my breathing rhythm is off.

583
00:34:19.182 --> 00:34:20.117
I'm sorry.

584
00:34:20.141 --> 00:34:23.635
This time, I'll really insert it.

585
00:34:37.450 --> 00:34:38.552
Darn it.

586
00:34:38.576 --> 00:34:41.904
Even fish don't breathe like that.

587
00:34:42.371 --> 00:34:43.891
Mr. Son.

588
00:34:43.915 --> 00:34:47.561
Are you really a licensed doctor?

589
00:34:47.585 --> 00:34:49.271
I'm getting a bit anxious.

590
00:34:49.295 --> 00:34:51.330
Goodness.

591
00:34:53.049 --> 00:34:55.235
- Oh, my! What are you doing?
- Kang-ho.

592
00:34:55.259 --> 00:34:56.737
My mom feels anxious.

593
00:34:56.761 --> 00:35:00.255
No, Kang-ho. That's dangerous. Give it to me.

594
00:35:00.389 --> 00:35:01.784
Are you really licensed?

595
00:35:01.808 --> 00:35:05.302
I really am! What's with you?

596
00:35:05.353 --> 00:35:07.623
Honey, tell him.

597
00:35:07.647 --> 00:35:09.124
He is.

598
00:35:09.148 --> 00:35:12.586
He'd never forge a license.

599
00:35:12.610 --> 00:35:15.839
Although he's forged his
resident registration card before.

600
00:35:15.863 --> 00:35:18.023
- What?
- What?

601
00:35:18.616 --> 00:35:20.776
I did it because I love you!

602
00:35:21.202 --> 00:35:23.764
I thought that was how I could have you!

603
00:35:23.788 --> 00:35:25.531
You're my woman!

604
00:35:25.915 --> 00:35:28.477
I thought you might not like
me because of our age gap.

605
00:35:28.501 --> 00:35:32.162
Oh, my. Is that really why?

606
00:35:32.380 --> 00:35:34.957
Did you want me that badly?

607
00:35:37.260 --> 00:35:38.362
Good grief.

608
00:35:38.386 --> 00:35:40.462
How is that relevant right now?

609
00:35:41.180 --> 00:35:42.658
He'll bleed if you stab him.

610
00:35:42.682 --> 00:35:46.510
That'll make me sad. Do you want me to be sad?

611
00:35:52.400 --> 00:35:53.585
Good boy.

612
00:35:53.609 --> 00:35:55.295
- Good boy.
- Good, Kang-ho.

613
00:35:55.319 --> 00:35:58.146
- Good boy.
- You must've been startled.

614
00:35:58.573 --> 00:35:59.716
- It's okay.
- I'm sorry.

615
00:35:59.740 --> 00:36:01.343
No, it's fine.

616
00:36:01.367 --> 00:36:05.362
You can feel that way if he
doesn't seem very trustworthy.

617
00:36:09.208 --> 00:36:11.687
By any chance, do you know...

618
00:36:11.711 --> 00:36:15.581
a man named Choi Mun-sik,
who owns a carp farm in Negi-ri?

619
00:36:22.430 --> 00:36:23.964
Hello?

620
00:36:24.515 --> 00:36:26.341
The realtor?

621
00:36:27.602 --> 00:36:28.829
Yes, one second.

622
00:36:28.853 --> 00:36:30.956
Was it Choi Mun-sik?

623
00:36:30.980 --> 00:36:32.916
- Isn't it Yoo Mun-sik?
- Not Lee?

624
00:36:32.940 --> 00:36:34.418
No, he's Choi Mun-sik.

625
00:36:34.442 --> 00:36:37.337
Yes, that huge carp farm
in Negi-ri. Of course I know.

626
00:36:37.361 --> 00:36:39.521
I've heard of him too.

627
00:36:39.614 --> 00:36:42.301
We know. Go on.

628
00:36:42.325 --> 00:36:44.026
What's with him?

629
00:36:45.703 --> 00:36:48.265
Mr. Son, go on and talk.

630
00:36:48.289 --> 00:36:50.726
Go on and talk, Mr. Son.

631
00:36:50.750 --> 00:36:52.227
Mr. Son...

632
00:36:52.251 --> 00:36:53.353
What's with him?

633
00:36:53.377 --> 00:36:56.440
So that Choi Mun-sik...

634
00:36:56.464 --> 00:36:59.026
I have to go to Seoul tomorrow.

635
00:36:59.050 --> 00:37:02.628
Seoul? What for?

636
00:37:03.554 --> 00:37:07.326
I'm sorry I keep asking
you guys for favors like this.

637
00:37:07.350 --> 00:37:11.121
Don't say that. We're neighbors.

638
00:37:11.145 --> 00:37:12.456
Don't worry.

639
00:37:12.480 --> 00:37:15.891
We'll give the pigs their
meals and Kang-ho his feed...

640
00:37:20.905 --> 00:37:24.509
We'll make sure Kang-ho has his
meal and the pigs their feed.

641
00:37:24.533 --> 00:37:26.818
Don't worry about a thing.

642
00:37:26.911 --> 00:37:29.765
Okay. Andrea has the farm covered,

643
00:37:29.789 --> 00:37:32.017
so please just look after Kang-ho.

644
00:37:32.041 --> 00:37:33.742
I'll get going then.

645
00:37:35.461 --> 00:37:37.105
Right.

646
00:37:37.129 --> 00:37:39.566
Kang-ho, I'll come back soon...

647
00:37:39.590 --> 00:37:42.626
after I get your stuff.

648
00:37:42.677 --> 00:37:45.489
I'll go with you and come back with you.

649
00:37:45.513 --> 00:37:47.130
Kang-ho.

650
00:37:48.766 --> 00:37:50.118
I told you, didn't I?

651
00:37:50.142 --> 00:37:54.081
The place is really dusty
because people are moving things.

652
00:37:54.105 --> 00:37:57.849
If dust gets into your body, you'll get sick.

653
00:37:57.984 --> 00:38:00.420
And that'll make me really sad.

654
00:38:00.444 --> 00:38:02.589
Do you want me to be sad?

655
00:38:02.613 --> 00:38:04.231
No.

656
00:38:08.869 --> 00:38:11.113
How soon will you come back?

657
00:38:13.457 --> 00:38:15.143
Around five o'clock.

658
00:38:15.167 --> 00:38:17.327
- Five o'clock.
- Yes.

659
00:38:17.586 --> 00:38:21.066
So be good and do as they say, okay?

660
00:38:21.090 --> 00:38:23.583
Make sure you study and exercise.

661
00:38:24.176 --> 00:38:26.238
- Okay.
- Good.

662
00:38:26.262 --> 00:38:28.431
<i><font color="#ffff00">We're All Jou-ri Family</font></i>

663
00:38:45.239 --> 00:38:47.092
I told you, didn't I?

664
00:38:47.116 --> 00:38:49.943
I told you he'd be doing something stupid.

665
00:38:50.202 --> 00:38:51.555
Why are you here?

666
00:38:51.579 --> 00:38:55.282
I heard Ms. Jin is coming back at five o'clock.

667
00:38:55.541 --> 00:38:57.200
Yes.

668
00:38:57.376 --> 00:39:00.772
So what time is five o'clock?

669
00:39:00.796 --> 00:39:04.318
We're only seven, so we can't read the clock,

670
00:39:04.342 --> 00:39:08.488
but I do know we have a
lot of time to play with him.

671
00:39:08.512 --> 00:39:10.324
- Yes!
- Yes!

672
00:39:10.348 --> 00:39:13.076
No, I can't play today.

673
00:39:13.100 --> 00:39:15.746
I have to study and exercise.

674
00:39:15.770 --> 00:39:18.138
Study? We'll help you.

675
00:39:18.190 --> 00:39:19.166
Exercise?

676
00:39:19.190 --> 00:39:22.169
You know we're experts at that.

677
00:39:22.193 --> 00:39:23.754
- Let's play!
- No! I can't!

678
00:39:23.778 --> 00:39:26.089
- Let's play!
- No! I can't play right now!

679
00:39:26.113 --> 00:39:27.507
No!

680
00:39:27.531 --> 00:39:30.275
No!

681
00:39:52.223 --> 00:39:56.927
<i>I left everything as it was,
because I thought you'd return soon.</i>

682
00:39:58.062 --> 00:40:01.124
But the realtor called and
said your lease has expired.

683
00:40:01.148 --> 00:40:02.709
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">Choi Kang-ho
Supreme Prosecutors' Office</font></i>

684
00:40:02.733 --> 00:40:04.935
{\an8}I'm sorry, Kang-ho.

685
00:40:13.369 --> 00:40:15.987
I've always wanted to visit this place.

686
00:40:18.040 --> 00:40:20.408
And I'm finally here.

687
00:40:31.095 --> 00:40:33.296
Are you taking this painting?

688
00:40:34.348 --> 00:40:36.049
This is...

689
00:40:36.142 --> 00:40:38.426
- Sure.
- Okay.

690
00:40:52.032 --> 00:40:54.693
He had some things here too.

691
00:40:57.405 --> 00:40:58.981
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">My Son, Jung Jong-gu, is Innocent!</font></i>

692
00:40:59.373 --> 00:41:01.333
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">I Denounce Prosecutor Choi Kang-ho!</font></i>

693
00:41:08.841 --> 00:41:10.819
He doesn't have a lot here.

694
00:41:10.843 --> 00:41:15.073
I put his personal belongings in here.

695
00:41:15.097 --> 00:41:16.283
And... Right.

696
00:41:16.307 --> 00:41:18.925
That plant pot is his too.

697
00:41:20.811 --> 00:41:23.540
It looks dead, so you can
leave it. We'll throw it out.

698
00:41:23.564 --> 00:41:25.292
No.

699
00:41:25.316 --> 00:41:28.253
It's not dead.

700
00:41:28.277 --> 00:41:30.714
The stem looks perfectly fine.

701
00:41:30.738 --> 00:41:32.981
I'll take it.

702
00:41:33.199 --> 00:41:35.734
Why didn't anyone water this?

703
00:41:36.827 --> 00:41:39.473
You can't go in there. Ma'am, please leave.

704
00:41:39.497 --> 00:41:41.099
Please.

705
00:41:41.123 --> 00:41:44.436
Where is Choi Kang-ho? Where is he?

706
00:41:44.460 --> 00:41:46.438
Woobyeok Group bought him off, right?

707
00:41:46.462 --> 00:41:47.981
That's why the case was acquitted!

708
00:41:48.005 --> 00:41:49.441
My daughter is the evidence!

709
00:41:49.465 --> 00:41:52.152
So why was the case
dismissed for lack of evidence?

710
00:41:52.176 --> 00:41:53.862
Ma'am, you can't do this here!

711
00:41:53.886 --> 00:41:56.781
If you don't stop, we'll arrest
you for obstruction of justice.

712
00:41:56.805 --> 00:41:57.908
Come on.

713
00:41:57.932 --> 00:41:59.451
Where is Choi Kang-ho?

714
00:41:59.475 --> 00:42:00.744
Please leave.

715
00:42:00.768 --> 00:42:02.746
Where is he?

716
00:42:02.770 --> 00:42:04.512
Please leave.

717
00:42:05.731 --> 00:42:09.726
What was that woman talking about?

718
00:42:14.156 --> 00:42:15.926
<i><font color="#ffff00">My Son, Jung Jong-gu, is Innocent!</font></i>

719
00:42:15.950 --> 00:42:17.618
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffff00">I Denounce Prosecutor Choi Kang-ho!</font></i>

720
00:42:27.169 --> 00:42:28.745
Excuse me.

721
00:42:29.338 --> 00:42:31.456
Why are you doing this?

722
00:42:31.966 --> 00:42:35.335
What did my son do so wrong
for you to do this here?

723
00:42:35.678 --> 00:42:38.573
Are you Prosecutor Choi Kang-ho's mother?

724
00:42:38.597 --> 00:42:41.091
Yes, I'm his mother.

725
00:42:41.141 --> 00:42:42.744
If you feel something is unfair,

726
00:42:42.768 --> 00:42:45.664
{\an8}you should go through the
legal process and get a retrial.

727
00:42:45.688 --> 00:42:49.599
{\an8}Why on earth are you
condemning my son so harshly?

728
00:42:51.026 --> 00:42:54.130
{\an8}What's wrong with you? Give it back!

729
00:42:54.154 --> 00:42:55.897
Give it back!

730
00:43:00.369 --> 00:43:02.013
My son...

731
00:43:02.037 --> 00:43:04.656
has a physical disability.

732
00:43:05.082 --> 00:43:09.187
He couldn't even hurt a fly.

733
00:43:09.211 --> 00:43:14.025
Your son knew that, but he
took a bribe from a rich man...

734
00:43:14.049 --> 00:43:16.486
and turned my son into a murderer.

735
00:43:16.510 --> 00:43:19.489
When my husband asked to hear him out,

736
00:43:19.513 --> 00:43:22.826
he said such harsh things and made him collapse.

737
00:43:22.850 --> 00:43:24.953
Your son is such a horrible person.

738
00:43:24.977 --> 00:43:28.456
Why did you give birth to such scum?

739
00:43:28.480 --> 00:43:29.499
Darn it!

740
00:43:29.523 --> 00:43:32.419
I'll make your son pay for it!

741
00:43:32.443 --> 00:43:36.146
I may forget to eat,

742
00:43:36.238 --> 00:43:41.026
but I won't forget to pray that...

743
00:43:41.076 --> 00:43:44.139
your son is punished and dies!

744
00:43:44.163 --> 00:43:46.474
You got that?

745
00:43:46.498 --> 00:43:49.200
Why should my son be punished?

746
00:43:49.376 --> 00:43:52.272
Your son should be punished for his crime.

747
00:43:52.296 --> 00:43:54.482
He was bribed?

748
00:43:54.506 --> 00:43:57.068
Why would he? What more could he want?

749
00:43:57.092 --> 00:44:00.128
Did you see him take it?

750
00:44:00.596 --> 00:44:03.700
If you say anything of this sort again,

751
00:44:03.724 --> 00:44:06.119
I'll make you pay for it.

752
00:44:06.143 --> 00:44:07.203
Understand?

753
00:44:07.227 --> 00:44:08.788
All right.

754
00:44:08.812 --> 00:44:10.040
Kill me.

755
00:44:10.064 --> 00:44:11.890
Just kill me.

756
00:44:12.483 --> 00:44:14.184
Kill me!

757
00:44:15.402 --> 00:44:17.464
My poor son...

758
00:44:17.488 --> 00:44:20.342
Now the next one is a science question.

759
00:44:20.366 --> 00:44:22.859
This insect lives in a flower.

760
00:44:23.370 --> 00:44:24.346
Butterfly.

761
00:44:24.370 --> 00:44:26.029
Wrong.

762
00:44:26.163 --> 00:44:27.766
- Bee.
- Wrong.

763
00:44:27.790 --> 00:44:29.184
What?

764
00:44:29.208 --> 00:44:32.812
Silverfish, cabbage
caterpillars, fleas, and aphids.

765
00:44:32.836 --> 00:44:34.356
Correct!

766
00:44:34.380 --> 00:44:36.608
I was actually talking
about napa cabbage flowers.

767
00:44:36.632 --> 00:44:39.125
Okay, ten points to Lee Seo-jin.

768
00:44:39.718 --> 00:44:42.447
Hey, Ye-jin, that's not right.

769
00:44:42.471 --> 00:44:45.632
He mentioned four. That means he gets 40 points.

770
00:44:48.602 --> 00:44:51.054
Okay. He can get 40 points.

771
00:44:51.647 --> 00:44:52.999
That could've been bad, right?

772
00:44:53.023 --> 00:44:56.017
Right, sure.

773
00:44:56.860 --> 00:44:59.422
Okay, the next one is a math question.

774
00:44:59.446 --> 00:45:02.967
Seo-jin had five apples.

775
00:45:02.991 --> 00:45:06.903
But Ye-jin stole three. How many are left?

776
00:45:07.454 --> 00:45:09.239
Kang-ho was faster.

777
00:45:11.041 --> 00:45:13.436
Simple larceny shall be
punished for up to six years,

778
00:45:13.460 --> 00:45:18.623
or by a fine under $10,000, under
Article 329 of the Criminal Act.

779
00:45:21.009 --> 00:45:24.379
What's simple larceny?

780
00:45:25.305 --> 00:45:26.965
What?

781
00:45:27.141 --> 00:45:29.384
What's simple larceny?

782
00:45:32.771 --> 00:45:34.514
Catch it!

783
00:45:35.357 --> 00:45:37.517
Oh, no. She's angry.

784
00:45:40.529 --> 00:45:42.799
You should've caught it.

785
00:45:42.823 --> 00:45:45.135
My mom sent it to us from the U.S.

786
00:45:45.159 --> 00:45:47.637
You almost lost it!

787
00:45:47.661 --> 00:45:49.639
- The U.S.?
- Yes, the U.S.

788
00:45:49.663 --> 00:45:50.557
Look.

